From 18157e460572217174c8f4f1c173779dd50772d8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 19:17:30 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 36/40] inline-3d(#625): let the runtime's XR_DXR_view_rig
 build the off-axis views

The three.js scene rig has never been right: the cube renders far too large,
far too high, and with huge disparity. Each fix so far corrected one term of
XRSession::UpdateInline3DViews' hand-rolled Kooima and moved the symptom
without curing it, because the whole derivation was the problem, not any one
term in it.

Stop re-deriving. The runtime already computes exactly these views, and it is
the authority on the two inputs the renderer can only reconstruct: the window's
true screen origin and the display's physical pixel pitch. It also already
knows how to scope that math to a sub-rect -- that is what a 3D zone IS ("the
rect IS the canvas": u_canvas_apply_to_metrics rebases the window metrics to
the zone rect and every downstream term, Kooima metres, eye offsets and the raw
channel, then describes the zone with zero further changes).

So an inline-3D element is just a zone. Per frame, for the scene element, the
browser now calls xrLocateViews with XrDisplayZoneDXR{rect} -> XrDisplayRigDXR
{virtualDisplayHeight} chained, and Blink installs the returned pose + fov
verbatim. ~95 lines of renderer-side projection math are deleted.

Key properties:

- The zone rect is the WEAVE rect, unchanged. u_canvas_rect is defined in
  client-window pixels, which is exactly the basis ReportInline3DRects already
  submits -- and that basis is proven correct every frame by the photos and
  video, which weave crisply at the right positions. The broken display-relative
  rebase (ClientToScreen + metres-per-pixel, consumed only by the deleted math)
  is gone, and with it the logical-vs-device-pixel hazard it carried.

- No frame loop is added. xrLocateViews validates only the space, the view
  config type and displayTime > 0 -- it does NOT require a running session -- so
  the weave client stays submit-only (no xrBeginSession/xrEndFrame) and cannot
  make the compositor present over the browser's own window. displayTime comes
  from XR_KHR_win32_convert_performance_counter_time.

- The session is a real present-owner (HWND + D3D11 binding), not a bridge
  relay, so rig_route_native applies. This matters: for bridge relays the
  runtime forces chained rig descriptors INERT (rig_type NONE) and hands back
  raw eyes, which would have looked exactly like the bug we are fixing.

Gated on view_rig + display_zones + the KHR time conversion all being present;
otherwise views come back empty and the session stays mono, as before.
